I have made this dish several times for a mixed crowd (people who love and people who hate brussel sprouts) . It gets two thumbs up from everyone. I make two changes - I carmelize the shallots until they are buttery (takes at least 30 minutes on low heat) and I omit the pine nuts ( I just don't think they are needed). I made it at Thanksgiving and my husband's family who are picky loved them.

