Rating: 4
I've made this recipe several times for my husband and I and we like it as it is. I think it really doesn't need bacon. I have used it as a base for grilled scallops (w/spicy seasoning and olive oil) and along side of grilled rock fish with marjoram butter (See "Red Snapper With Lemon Marjoram Butter"). Really nice combinations. I use my Cuisinart to slice the sprouts very thin (the thinnest setting). The sweetness of the shallots and the lemon juice balance out the bitterness of the sprouts. Note that it's important to remove the dark out leaves of the sprouts. Dark leave produce the really bitter taste that some people have complained about.

