Rating: 4
I have made this recipe many times over the last few years, and all have loved it and asked for the recipe. I do not use butter, I crisp up finely chopped pancetta in a fry pan first, then remove it from the frypan and crumble it, set it aside,then pour off most of the grease from the pan before I saute the shallots in the pancetta oil,then follow the recipe to the end. At the very end I add the crumbed pancetta just before serving

