Rating: 0
My technique for slicing brussels sprouts: cut off the tough bottom stalk and remove loose and tough outer leaves. Stand on flat bottom and slice off the outside edges until you are left with the core. Now slice off the upper one-third of the remaining core and discard the rest. You are left with the most tender parts of the sprout, and everything cooks uniformly since it is the same density. This is no different than what you would do with a cabbage.

